On September 4, 2018, President Donald J. Trump announced three nominations and appointments. The first is John Mark Pommersheim of Florida, who has been nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Tajikistan. Pommersheim is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has been an American diplomat since 1990. He currently serves as the Deputy Chief of Mission at the United States Embassy in Astana, Kazakhstan.

The second appointment is Earle D. Litzenberger of California, who has been nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Azerbaijan. Litzenberger is also a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as Senior Advisor in the Bureau of Political-Military Affairs at the Department of State.

Lastly, President Trump announced his intent to appoint Kay Coles James of Virginia to be a Member of the Women's Suffrage Centennial Commission.